other_tests.procedure_name: CT of the abdomen and pelvis with and without intravenous contrast
other_tests.findings: An abnormally mucosally-enhancing 10 mm in diameter appendix with associated periappendiceal stranding, findings compatible with acute appendicitis. The tip is in contact with the transverse colon and appears adherent. Cholelithiasis noted without secondary signs of cholecystitis. A 2.2 x 3.3 cm predominantly hypoattenuating liver lesion with peripheral nodular enhancement, features compatible with a benign hemangioma. Small amount of fluid tracking along the right paracolic gutter.
